modules.description: Provides HTTP request methods including GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, and PATCH with support for custom headers, request bodies, and chunked encoding. Operates on URI endpoints, HTTP methods, and Cohttp's request/response structures, including bodies managed via Lwt. Used for sending structured HTTP requests, handling form data with post_form, and managing asynchronous network interactions with context-aware connections.

Provides functions to read and write Git objects including blobs, trees, commits, and tags, along with pack files and indexes. Supports operations like making pack files position-independent and generating index files from pack data. Enables expanding a commit's filesystem and manipulating Git objects through a unified API.

handles HTTP communication through methods like GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, and PATCH, supporting custom headers, request bodies, and asynchronous operations via Lwt. It works with URI endpoints, Cohttp request/response types, and manages data transmission including form submissions and chunked encoding. Operations include sending structured requests, parsing responses, and handling network interactions in a non-blocking manner. Examples include fetching resources, submitting forms, and updating data through RESTful APIs.
